  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1845777428" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1845777428" />
    <a title="Marwan Shalaby" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12626408-marwan-shalaby"><img alt="Marwan Shalaby" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1845777428?book_show_action=true">Jul 13, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Marwan Shalaby" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Marwan Shalaby" href="/user/show/12626408-marwan-shalaby">Marwan Shalaby</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12626408-marwan-shalaby?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1845777428" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4361174279003244573">While anarchy is always synonymous to chaos and lawlessness, and while Anarchists are sometimes perceived as delusional utopians. This book generally discusses the basic principles of Anarchist thinking, with a special focus on Anarcho-Syndicalism, and puts Anarchist values as viable guiding principles for a fairer, freer and more &quot;human&quot; society. Drawing on the paragons of liberal thinking such as Rousseau, Von Humboldt, John Stuart Mill and Adam Smith (Yes, the father-of-capitalism-Adam Smith)</span>
  <span id="freeText4361174279003244573" style="display:none">While anarchy is always synonymous to chaos and lawlessness, and while Anarchists are sometimes perceived as delusional utopians. This book generally discusses the basic principles of Anarchist thinking, with a special focus on Anarcho-Syndicalism, and puts Anarchist values as viable guiding principles for a fairer, freer and more "human" society. Drawing on the paragons of liberal thinking such as Rousseau, Von Humboldt, John Stuart Mill and Adam Smith (Yes, the father-of-capitalism-Adam Smith), Chomsky makes the case that Anarchism is the system that is truest to Western Enlightenment values.<br /><br />Anarchy is not about entirely abolishing authority, it is not about abolishing private property, it is also not about destroying individuality. But it's quite the opposite, it's about living in a society where authority, be it on the local or the familial levels, must be justified. And the burden of proof to justify this authority falls on its bearer. It's about maximizing individual freedom, aiming for maximum self-fulfillment, while having broader responsibilities to the community around you. It's about abolishing any sort of predetermined hierarchy, and rebuilding the society from the bottom up, with active participation in the decision making, in a truly democratic fashion. <br /><br />The book shook me, challenged so many core concepts and structures that were seemingly commonsensical and, in a sense, unassailable. For example: "Why humans should be productive?" and "Is working for money moral?". And while I came out with more questions than answers, this was definitely a very intellectually stimulating read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4361174279003244573" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

